The Shining Path, a Maoist guerrilla group, sought to overthrow Peru's
elected government and install a peasant and worker state.  It was
successful among the Indians in the Andes and extended guerrilla
warfare to the jungles and cities.  By 1994, however, many leaders
were jailed and a second faction formed.</SUM>
